title: Google\Cloud\DataCatalog\V1\Entry
name: Entry
description:
Entry Metadata.

A Data Catalog Entry resource represents another resource in Google Cloud Platform (such as a BigQuery dataset or a Pub/Sub topic) or outside of Google Cloud Platform. Clients can use the linked_resource field in the Entry resource to refer to the original resource ID of the source system. An Entry resource contains resource details, such as its schema. An Entry can also be used to attach flexible metadata, such as a [Tag][google.cloud.datacatalog.v1.Tag].

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.datacatalog.v1.Entry

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The Data Catalog resource name of the entry in URL format. Example: * projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}/entryGroups/{entry_group_id}/entries/{entry_id} Note that this Entry and its child resources may not actually be stored in the location in this name.

params.name: data.linked_resource
params.description: The resource this metadata entry refers to. For Google Cloud Platform resources, linked_resource is the full name of the resource. For example, the linked_resource for a table resource from BigQuery is: * //bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/projectId/datasets/datasetId/tables/tableId Output only when Entry is of type in the EntryType enum. For entries with user_specified_type, this field is optional and defaults to an empty string.

params.name: data.type
params.description: The type of the entry. Only used for Entries with types in the EntryType enum.

params.name: data.user_specified_type
params.description: Entry type if it does not fit any of the input-allowed values listed in EntryType enum above. When creating an entry, users should check the enum values first, if nothing matches the entry to be created, then provide a custom value, for example "my_special_type". user_specified_type strings must begin with a letter or underscore and can only contain letters, numbers, and underscores; are case insensitive; must be at least 1 character and at most 64 characters long. Currently, only FILESET enum value is allowed. All other entries created through Data Catalog must use user_specified_type.

params.name: data.integrated_system
params.description: Output only. This field indicates the entry's source system that Data Catalog integrates with, such as BigQuery or Pub/Sub.

params.name: data.user_specified_system
params.description: This field indicates the entry's source system that Data Catalog does not integrate with. user_specified_system strings must begin with a letter or underscore and can only contain letters, numbers, and underscores; are case insensitive; must be at least 1 character and at most 64 characters long.

params.name: data.gcs_fileset_spec
params.description: Specification that applies to a Cloud Storage fileset. This is only valid on entries of type FILESET.

params.name: data.bigquery_table_spec
params.description: Specification that applies to a BigQuery table. This is only valid on entries of type TABLE.

params.name: data.bigquery_date_sharded_spec
params.description: Specification for a group of BigQuery tables with name pattern [prefix]YYYYMMDD. Context: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/partitioned-tables#partitioning_versus_sharding.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Display information such as title and description. A short name to identify the entry, for example, "Analytics Data - Jan 2011". Default value is an empty string.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Entry description, which can consist of several sentences or paragraphs that describe entry contents. Default value is an empty string.

params.name: data.schema
params.description: Schema of the entry. An entry might not have any schema attached to it.

params.name: data.source_system_timestamps
params.description: Timestamps about the underlying resource, not about this Data Catalog entry. Output only when Entry is of type in the EntryType enum. For entries with user_specified_type, this field is optional and defaults to an empty timestamp.
